# Personal Finance Manager — Cline Rules

## Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14 App Router (frontend only, no backend)
- Language: TypeScript
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- State: Zustand
- Data fetching: TanStack Query (React Query)
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod
- Charts: Recharts
- Icons: Lucide React
- Mock data: all data is mocked, no real API calls

## Pastel Neutral Palette
- Background: #FAF8F5 (warm cream)
- Card surface: #F2EDE8 (soft stone)
- Income accent: #B5E2CF (sage mint)
- Expense accent: #F2B8C6 (blush pink)
- Info/chart: #B3D9F5 (sky blue)
- Budget warning: #F7CEAD (warm peach)
- Text primary: #2C2C2A
- Text secondary: #6B6B68
- Border: #E2DDD8

## Mock Data
- All data lives in src/data/ as TypeScript constants
- Use hardcoded faker-style records, rich enough to make the UI look real (at least 10–20 records per entity)
- No database, no API calls, no localStorage (unless explicitly requested)

## Folder Structure
src/
  app/            → Next.js App Router pages
  components/     → UI components (organized by module)
    ui/           → atoms: Button, Card, Badge, Input...
    layout/       → Sidebar, Navbar, BottomNav
    dashboard/    → DashboardSummary, RecentTransactions...
    wallet/       → WalletCard, WalletList...
    transaction/  → TransactionItem, TransactionForm...
    category/     → CategoryBadge, CategoryPicker...
    budget/       → BudgetCard, BudgetProgress...
    profile/      → ProfileCard, ProfileForm...
  data/           → mock data (users, wallets, transactions...)
  hooks/          → custom hooks
  lib/            → utils, formatters, constants
  store/          → Zustand stores
  types/          → TypeScript interfaces

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (TransactionItem.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase prefixed with use (useTransactions.ts)
- Pages: kebab-case folders, page.tsx inside
- Types: PascalCase interfaces (Transaction, Wallet...)

## Code Style
- One component per file
- Always default export the main component
- Use "use client" only when interactivity is needed
- Long Tailwind class strings → extract into cn() helper
- No `any` types — always type fully

## UI Rules
- All cards: rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-[#E2DDD8]
- Consistent spacing: p-4 for small cards, p-6 for large cards
- Income → mint background #B5E2CF, text #2A6B4E
- Expense → blush background #F2B8C6, text #7B3352
- Loading skeletons: bg-[#F2EDE8] animate-pulse
